<subSubSection lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1409,2010]" lastBlockId="54.[151,1436,151,680]" lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1769,1794]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus box="[423,526,1769,1793]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
; in parentheses 
<typeStatus box="[702,801,1770,1794]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">paratype</typeStatus>
, n = 1; in square brackets specimen from IR20-2011, n = 1) — Dorsal and ventral shields anteriorly fused; dorsal shield (
<figureCitation box="[880,983,1805,1829]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1558,1581]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,743,1511]" captionTargetId="figure-482@54.[151,1436,733,1537]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 39A–B. Haloaxonopsis salina sp. nov., holotype male, IR14-2011: A = dorsal shield; B = ventral shield. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 39A</figureCitation>
) L/W 513 (538) [470]/389 (322) [345], with seven pairs of glandularia (the seventh pair inconspicuous, flanking the excretory pore); postocularia well distanced from anterior margin; colour pattern indistinct; extending beyond posterior margin of the ventral shield; eye pigment well developed; excretory pore located at posterior end of dorsal shield. Ventral shield (
<figureCitation box="[1222,1321,1914,1938]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1558,1581]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,743,1511]" captionTargetId="figure-482@54.[151,1436,733,1537]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 39A–B. Haloaxonopsis salina sp. nov., holotype male, IR14-2011: A = dorsal shield; B = ventral shield. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 39B</figureCitation>
) L/W 519 (503) [494]/459 (413) [469], slightly truncate at anterior end, lateral margins rounded. Gnathosomal bay L 134 (136) [125]. Venter without a ridge on each side extending posteriorly from the region of insertion of the IV-L. Three pairs of 'wheel-like' acetabula (
<figureCitation box="[592,745,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1824,1847]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,280,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-67@59.[151,1436,267,1803]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 43A–F. SEM photos of Haloaxonopsis salina sp. nov. (A–D = paratype male, E–F = paratype female), IR14-2011: A, C, E-F = genital field; B, D = details of genital field." pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Figs. 43A 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[708,722,152,176]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">–</emphasis>
D
</figureCitation>
), arranged in an arc; distance between most lateral pair of wheel-like Ac 107 (103) [113]. Gonopore extending beyond the anterior pair of weel-like acetabula, L/W 45 (44) [30]/34 (30) [26]; gonopore flanked by several small setae. Ejaculatory complex (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1159,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,213,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-52@56.[151,1436,193,1971]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 41A–E. Haloaxonopsis salina sp. nov., holotype male, IR14-2011: A–B = palp; C = I-L-5 and -6; D = ejaculatory complex; E = IV-L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 41D</figureCitation>
) L 142 (143) [135]. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[159,251,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,213,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-52@56.[151,1436,193,1971]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 41A–E. Haloaxonopsis salina sp. nov., holotype male, IR14-2011: A–B = palp; C = I-L-5 and -6; D = ejaculatory complex; E = IV-L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs. 41</figureCitation>
A-B): total L 257 (256) [244], dL: P-1, 42 (42) [37]; P-2, 72 (69) [67]; P-3, 32 (32) [31]; P-4, 82 (83) [80]; P-5, 29 (30) [29]; L P-2/P-4 ratio, 0.88 (0.83) [0.84]; ventral margin of P-2 convex, middle of ventral side of P-4 expanded, bearing a hair-like seta lying on a small pointed tubercle. Gnathosoma vL 120 (122) [103]. Legs: dL of I-L-4-6 (
<figureCitation box="[251,356,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,213,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-52@56.[151,1436,193,1971]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 41A–E. Haloaxonopsis salina sp. nov., holotype male, IR14-2011: A–B = palp; C = I-L-5 and -6; D = ejaculatory complex; E = IV-L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 41C</figureCitation>
): 72 [65], 88 (88) [84], 94 (96) [85]; dL of IV-L (
<figureCitation box="[932,1036,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,213,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-52@56.[151,1436,193,1971]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 41A–E. Haloaxonopsis salina sp. nov., holotype male, IR14-2011: A–B = palp; C = I-L-5 and -6; D = ejaculatory complex; E = IV-L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 41E</figureCitation>
): 85 [83], 112 (115) [104], 85 (90) [79], 104 (108) [98], 122 (119) [112], 115 (117) [110]; swimming setae numbers: II-L-5, 3; III-L-4, 2; III-L-5, 3; IV-L-4, 2; IV-L-5 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Female (
